### Wasla API HTTP Requests
### You can run these directly if you have the "REST Client" extension installed in VS Code.

@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000

### 1. Health Check
# Ensure the API is running and connected to all Database Shards.
GET {{baseUrl}}/health
Accept: application/json

---

### 2. Create a Short URL (Shorten Endpoint)
# Submits a long URL to generate a short ID, save it to the DB, and cache it in Redis.
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/shorten
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "longUrl": "https://www.youtube.com/"
}

###

### 3. Create another Short URL
# Generating a few helps us verify that the shard routing distributes across both DBs.
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/shorten
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "longUrl": "https://www.typescriptlang.org/docs/"
}

###

### 4. Debug Shard Resolution (Optional)
# Enter the shortId returned from the requests above to see which DB shard it belongs to
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/debug/shard/pO8Pe4RI
Accept: application/json

---

### 5. Redirect Endpoint (Phase 5 - To Be Implemented)
# Tests the cache-aside pattern and redirect logic once we build the GET /:id route
GET {{baseUrl}}/cOi4Baei
